HEADWORD: Compsognathus
<hw>Comp*sog"na*thus</hw>
<pr>(k⟦ocr⟧mp*s⟦ocr⟧g"n⟦adot⟧*th⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>kompo`s</grk> elegant, pretty + <grk>gna`qos</grk>
jaw.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of carnivorous Dinosauria
found in the Jurassic formation with a slender body, and remarkable for
having several birdlike features. It reached a length of 30 inches when
adult.</def>⟦br⟧
